subSubSection.paragraph:
Females (
Figs. 3–4
): Ground colour gray or light brown, sometimes with vertically elongated, diffuse darkgray to black blotches, forming small bars. One or two black spots on anterocentral portion of flank. Opercular region bright light blue. Iris light yellow, with inconspicuous vertical gray bar through centre of the eye. Fins hyaline. Dorsal and anal fins with small gray spots, sometimes inconspicuous. Supra and suborbital band light gray.
